  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Watchdog for Environmental Management Act 2004</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LEAT envisages undertaking a rigorous awareness raising campaign to the Tanzanian people about the principles, rights, and duties enshrined in environmental management legislation. This will enable the Tanzanian people to have a firm understanding of these principles, their environmental rights, and their duty to take action to protect the environment on one hand and take part in environmental decision-making processes on the other. By doing so, the Tanzanian people will ensure that the principles enshrined in EMA become a living reality and the Tanzanian environment is not degraded. 

The overall goal of the project is promote the enforcement of Environmental Management Act, 2004 in Tanzania through environmental and constitutional rights awareness raising and public interest litigation campaigns</narrative>
  </description>
